### PR summary [38a1b49a52](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/19927/commits/38a1b49a526fbb16979f33a8e518b841fe2c5f24)

#### Import changes for modified files

No significant changes to the import graph


<details><summary>Import changes for all files</summary>

|Files|Import difference|
|-|-|

</details>

---

#### Declarations diff

No declarations were harmed in the making of this PR! üêô
<details>
  <summary>You can run this locally as follows</summary>


```bash
## summary with just the declaration names:
./scripts/declarations_diff.sh <optional_commit>

## more verbose report:
./scripts/declarations_diff.sh long <optional_commit>
```
</details>

The doc-module for `script/declarations_diff.sh` contains some details about this script.

---

<details><summary>No changes to technical debt.</summary>

You can run this locally as
```
./scripts/technical-debt-metrics.sh pr_summary
```
* The `relative` value is the weighted *sum* of the differences with weight given by the *inverse* of the current value of the statistic.
* The `absolute` value is the `relative` value divided by the total sum of the inverses of the current values (i.e. the weighted *average* of the differences).
</details>

Hmm, the default badge is much bigger than the others: 
![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/eb212959-e04f-426e-8620-7c7fb97aa574)
Would it be possible to also add a big standalone button in the Installation section please, right above the same for Gitpod? Thanks!!

As far as I can tell there's no existing badge that matches the others at the top (and yes, this is an official GitHub badge).

It lines up terribly side by side with the Gitpod badge, so this might be the best we get without designing our own:
![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/ead233ba-1e1c-4667-862a-c431de512061)

Pull request successfully merged into master.

Build succeeded:

  * [Lint style](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/actions/runs/12307120924/job/34350176460)
nit: might look nicer to have these two buttons on the same line, by deleting the blank line between them.
It does not. They don't line up whatsoever.
